ZH: 我们需要勇气去踏出舒适区。
EN: We need courage to step out of our comfort zone.

ZH: 昨天他终于踏出了自己的房间。
EN: Yesterday, he finally stepped out of his room.

ZH: 她毅然决然地踏出了人生的新篇章。
EN: She resolutely stepped into a new chapter of her life.

ZH: 我愿意为了追求自己的梦想而踏出安逸的生活。
EN: I'm willing to step out of a comfortable life to pursue my dreams.

ZH: 他怯于踏出一步，错失了一个好机会。
EN: He hesitated to take a step forward and missed a good opportunity.

ZH: 在未来的道路上，我们需要一起踏出前行。
EN: On the road ahead, we need to step out together.

ZH: 踏出舒适区意味着不断挑战自己。
EN: Stepping out of your comfort zone means constantly challenging yourself.

ZH: 即使有困难，我们也要勇敢踏出第一步。
EN: Even in the face of difficulties, we must bravely take the first step.

ZH: 踏出失败的阴影，向成功迈进。
EN: Step out of the shadow of failure and move towards success.

ZH: 每一个重要决策都需要我们勇往直前、踏出一步。
EN: Every important decision requires us to move forward and take a step.

ZH: 必须踏出家门，才能体验真正的自由和冒险。
EN: You have to go out of your house to experience true freedom and adventure.

ZH: 踏出一步，你就可以发现新的世界。
EN: Step out and you will discover a new world.

ZH: 勇于踏出新领域，你将收获更多的机遇。
EN: Dare to step into new territories, and you will gain more opportunities.

ZH: 我决定踏出旅行的第一步，追求未知的冒险和发现。
EN: I decided to take the first step of the journey, pursuing unknown adventures and discoveries.

ZH: 人生就是要不断踏出新的边界，寻找新的可能性。
EN: Life is about constantly pushing boundaries, seeking new possibilities.

ZH: 他下定决心踏出故乡，去追求更好的生活。
EN: He made up his mind to leave his hometown and seek a better life.

ZH: 我们要踏出固有的思维模式，接受不同的观点。
EN: We need to step out of our fixed mindset and embrace different perspectives.

ZH: 不要怕踏出失败的一步，失败是成功的前奏。
EN: Don't be afraid to take a step forward even if it leads to failure; failure is a prelude to success.

ZH: 踏出勇气，走向未知的道路。
EN: Step out with courage and walk on the path of the unknown.

ZH: 只有踏出了舒适区，我们才能真正成长。
EN: Only by stepping out of our comfort zone can we truly grow.
